(S1)

Here,  is the orientation angle of the long axis of the cell body (figure 1A), which implies that ( ) characterizes flagellar shapes with respect to a material frame of the cell body. By averaging the tangent angle profiles (s, t) over a full beat cycle, we define a time-averaged flagellar shape characterized by a tangent angle (s). To characterize variations from this mean flagellar shape, we employed a kernel principal component analysis (PCA) [29]. The kernel used to compute the Gram matrix D for the kernel PCA must account for the 2 -periodicity of the tangent angle data and was taken as Dij =
